            <!-- Modal content. Help text explaining BRAN# -->
            <div class="modal fade" id="barnmodal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                    <div class="modal-content">
                        <div class="modal-header">
                            <span class="h6 modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel">What is "Business Area Reference Number" ?</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="modal-body">
                            <p>The Business Area Reference Number, also known as BARN, is a State Farm assigned number specific to a business area that is used to identify a trading partner. If multiple business areas have interactions with a particular trading partner, then this trading partner could have multiple BARNs.</p>
                            <p>
                                <b>Note: </b>Not all business areas assign a BARN to their trading partners so if this is true in your case then you will not enter a BARN.
                            </p>
                            <p>Within this application, the Business Area Reference Number is assigned to a particular role not to the trading partner. This is because a role in this application represents a business area. Since each business area can assign it's own BARN for the trading partner we need to collect the BARN on the role not on the trading partner.</p>
                            <p>Here is an example to help clarify.</p>
                            <p>Assume you are from the Select Service Consolidator business area and you want to add the role Select Service Consolidator to trading partner ABC Auto Repair. Let's say, in your business area you have assigned ABC123456 as the BARN to this trading partner. When you add the role Select Service Consolidator to ABC Auto Repair, then you will want to put ABC123456 in the Business Area Reference Number field. This way if another area like EFT Receipt Inquiry wants to add the role EFT Receipt Inquiry to ABC Auto Repair, then they will be able to assign their BARN to this trading partner by assigning it to the EFT Receipt Inquiry role.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="modal-footer">
                            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-secondary align-content-center" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
